comment_data.body: I'm not sure why flutter bug report is saying "No Flutter sdk configured.". I do have it configured. When I open Languages & Frameworks/Flutter, SDK path is populated and points to valid flutter sdk repo.

Hmm, looks like may be as a result of changed expectations from https://github.com/flutter/flutter/pull/14061.

Thanks for the report!
From looking at the source, I'm not sure why this is crashing - we do have hardening around the file existing. It's not clear how many users this is hitting.
FWIW I also just hit this.
Speculatively closing, but we'll keep an eye on this. If we get many reports, we'll need to patch it into M21.

title: Intellij reported that flutter plugin crashed.
